Package Custom_CollectionsED.list.arrayLists

Class ArrayList<T>

java.lang.Object
Custom_CollectionsED.list.arrayLists.ArrayList<T>
Type Parameters:
T - The data type to be stored in the list, must be comparable.
All Implemented Interfaces:
ListADT<T>, Iterable<T>
Direct Known Subclasses:
ArrayOrderedList, ArrayUnorderedList
public abstract class ArrayList<T> extends Object implements ListADT<T>
This class is an implementation of the List data structure, with the usage of arrays as a support for the structure. It implements the ListADT interface.

    • remove

      public T remove(T element)
        The remove method :
      • check if the arrayList is empty;
      • iterates through the entire array looking to find the index of the element given as a parameter in the array;
      • after finding the index for the element to be removed, proceeds to move all element in the array one spot to the right, beginning at the index of the element to be removed, thus eliminating it from the array;
      • turns the last spot in the array into null ( eliminating duplicates for the last element ); updates the counter variable;
      • updates the modCount variable;
      Specified by:
      remove in interface ListADT<T>
      Parameters:
      element - element to be removed
      Returns:
      the removedElement from the array
      Throws:
      NoSuchElementException - if the element doesn't exist in the list.
